Calling all pop culture fans! Hot Toys Summer Showcase has kicked off its first stop at Hong Kong yesterday. Have a closer at some of the highly-accurate life-size statues, figure and collectibles that will create an unforgettable experience. Stay tuned as there’s more to come!

#HotToys #SummerShowcase2021

Hot Toys Summer Showcase 2021 @ Hong Kong
Date: 16th JUL – 15th AUG, 2021
Address: Shop G12-14, Fashion Walk, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
Opening Hours: 12:00pm – 9:00pm

Marty McFly and Doc Brown have traveled to Japan from Hill Valley! Join our favorite duo pair from Back To The Future trilogy for a time traveling exhibit – “Back To The Future: Retro Sapiens” by Hot Toys in Tokyo until the end of this October. Features a series of highly-accurate figures & collectibles including prototypes of Marty McFly, Doc Brown and DeLorean Time Machine as 1/6th scale collectible figures and vehicle; authentic costumes & signature props directly from the productions; also a pop-up store for fans to enjoy the fun from unique collections. 
 
Visit this one-of-a-kind exhibit to pick up the 1/6th scale Marty McFly figure from Back to the Future collection and make pre-orders on the newly debuted figures based on the last installment of the trilogy, as well as 1/6th scale Doc Brown figure with extra Plutonium from Back to the Future I for your timeless display! Don’t miss out on this special opportunity to bring home your beloved characters and the iconic time machine as adorable @Cosbaby and CosRider collection! 
 
Speed up to 88mph to meet everyone in the “Back To The Future” exhibition now! #BTTF #BackToTheFuture 

Back To The Future: Retro Sapiens | Tokyo, Japan
Date:  18th Sept – 31st Oct, 2021 
Venue: Hot Toys Flagship Store, Toy Sapiens Tokyo, Ichigo Jingumae Bldg 1st Floor, Jingumae 6-25-16, Shibuya-Ku, Tokyo 150-0001

node.text:
“Your future is whatever you make it, so make it a good one!” – Doc Brown

Since making its debut thirty years ago, Back to the Future has blown fans and audiences away with its humor, heart, and time-traveling antics. The final installment of the timeless trilogy finds Marty McFly digging the trusty DeLorean out of a mineshaft and looking up Doc Brown in the Wild West of 1885. But when their time machine breaks down, the travelers are stranded in a land of spurs. 

Today, Hot Toys is delighted to introduce the brand new 1/6th scale Doc Brown collectible figure inspired by Back to the future III. 

Beautifully crafted based on the appearance of Christopher Lloyd in the old west as Dr. Emmett Brown in the movie, the latest Doc Brown collectible figure features a newly developed head sculpt with cowboy hat; greatly detailed costume with refined tailoring, the coat and scarf to recreate the signature look as seen in front of the clock tower; highly-detailed weapons and accessories including rifle, pistol, miniature time machine, pocket watch, communicator with battery and a figure stand.

The scientist in old west outfit will surely be a great addition for your time-traveling display. 

#HotToys #Collectibles #SixthScale #BacktotheFuture #BTTF3 #DocBrown #DrEmmettBrown #ChristopherLloyd

“I brought you a little souvenir.” – Doc Brown

Stranded in 1955, Marty McFly learns about the death of his eccentric scientist friend Doc Brown in 1885 and must travel back in time to save him. With no fuel readily available for the DeLorean time machine, the two must figure how to escape the Old West before Emmett is murdered.

A lot has changed in thirty years, but the love for Back to the Future has not dwindled. Today, Hot Toys is excited to introduce the new 1/6th scale Marty McFly collectible figure based on the final installment of Back to the Future trilogy.

The stunningly detailed collectible figure is specially crafted based on the appearance of Michael J. Fox as Marty McFly in Back to the Future III, featuring a newly developed head sculpt and cowboy hat with amazing likeness, screen accurate costume, a brown patterned poncho, cowboy scarf, an array of weapon and accessories including pistol, bullet proof stove plate, pie dish, framed photo from Doc Brown, photo of Doc’s tomb, communicator with battery, hoverboard and a figure stand! 

Recreate timeless scenes with the Marty McFly figure!

#HotToys #Collectibles #SixthScale #BacktotheFuture #BTTF3 #MartyMcFly #MichaelJFox

One of Marvel’s greatest and most complex characters, the lethal protector Venom is returning to the big screen. Adding variety to the Venom: Let There Be Carnage collection, Hot Toys is presenting a brand new Venom and Carnage Cosbaby (S) Bobble-Head Collectible Set. Each collectible measure approximately 9.5 - 11cm tall comes with Bobble-Head design.

Venom Cosbaby recreates the eponymous alien symbiote through a skillfully painted body with muscles, white vines, and his long protruding tongue sticking out from an evil, grinning, fang-filled mouth, accompanied by a venom maw rising on ground; whereas Carnage Cosbaby recreates the symbiote with a crimson body, black vines, bayonet-like teeth, and weaponized arm, fighting against Venom in the mid air with a Carnage maw. 

Don’t miss out on this awesome @Cosbaby set!

Though the armor gets a few aesthetic changes, James Rhodes’ suit is still highly weaponised, with massive machine guns mounted on arms and shoulders. Long awaited by fans, Hot Toys is excited to share with fans the final product of 1/6th scale diecast Iron Patriot collectible figure from the Avengers: Endgame collections. 

Specially crafted based on the appearance of Don Cheadle as James Rhodes/Iron Patriot in Avengers: Endgame, the 1/6th scale diescast figure features two interchangeable head sculpts including a newly developed head sculpt and a helmet head with LED light-up function; metallic blue and reddish-orange painted armor with streamline armor design; LED light-up chest Arc Reactor and repulsors; Iron Patriot’s articulated weapons including back-mounted cannons and shoulder-mounted missile launchers, and a themed figure base.

Enjoy a closer look at the heavily armored figure of Iron Patriot!

In the universe we know, Steve Rogers was the the first Avenger, Captain America. In this universe, Steve has never taken the super soldier serum. Instead, he piloted a suit designed by Howard Stark, becoming known as “The Hydra Stomper”. 

Adding onto the newly debuted What If…? Cosbaby series, today Hot Toys is delighted to officially present the new Hydra Stomper & Steve Rogers Cosbaby (S) Bobble-Head Collectible Set to explore the endless, multiple possibilities of the Marvel Cinematic Universe! Collectible stands approximately 10 – 15cm in height. 

Steve Rogers joins the battle with The Hydra Stomper armored suit; make sure to open up the helmet of Hydra Stomper and let Steve Rogers to pilot the gigantic suit. The Hydra Stomper is approximately 15cm tall, and Steve Rogers Cosbaby is approximately 10cm with bobble head function and interchangeable arms for salute pose.

Fans of What If…? shouldn’t miss the chance to add the adorable Cosbaby to your collection!

“Her one choice gave birth to a whole new history and gave the multiverse a new hero.” – The Watcher

What If… Captain Carter was the First Avenger? After an ambush in the lab, Peggy Carter steps in and takes the Super Soldier serum and uses her newfound power and strength to charge right into battle. 

Inspired by Marvel Studios’ What If? animation series, Hot Toys proudly presents today Captain Carter as highly-detailed 1/6th scale collectible figure from another universe.

Beautifully crafted based on the appearance of Captain Carter in the animation series, the figure features a newly developed head sculpt and interchangeable brown curly hair sculptures with stunning likeness, finely tailored outfit in red, blue and white color scheme, Captain Carter’s signature shield, sword, pistol, and figure stand.

Let your Marvel collection grow today by adding the new Captain Carter 1/6th scale collectible figure!
